ar on Sermons: Umar warns against greed, anger, and dishonesty","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 29, 2020","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, used to say to people in his sermons, \u201cThose among you have succeeded who are protected from whims, greed, and anger. There is no good in anything less than truthful speech.\u201d Source: al-Zuhd li-Abi\u0304 Da\u0304wu\u0304d 48 Grade: Jayyid\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25082,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/07\/19\/harsh-make-me-rifq\/","url_meta":{"origin":34642,"position":1},"title":"Umar on Dua: I am harsh, so make me gentle","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"July 19, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Shaddad ibn Aws reported: Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, said, \u201cO Allah, I am weak, so make me strong. I am harsh, so make me gentle. I am miserly, so make me generous.\u201d Source: Mus\u0323annaf Ibn Abi\u0304 Shaybah 5179 \u0639\u0646 \u0634\u062f\u0627\u062f \u0628\u0646 \u0623\u0648\u0633 \u0642\u0627\u0644 \u0639\u0645\u0631 \u0628\u0646\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":28842,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/05\/08\/masters-knowledge-act-upon\/","url_meta":{"origin":34642,"position":2},"title":"Ibn Salam on &#8216;Ilm: Masters of knowledge act upon what they know","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 8, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"\u2018Ubaydullah ibn Umar reported: Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, said to Abdullah ibn Salam, \u201cWho are the masters of knowledge?\u201d Abdullah said, \u201cThose who act upon what they know.\u201d Umar said, \u201cWhat nullifies knowledge in the hearts of men?\u201d Abdullah said, \u201cGreed.\u201d Source: Sunan al-Da\u0304rimi\u0304 595\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Scholars \u0627\u0644\u0639\u0644\u0645\u0627\u0621","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/scholars-ulema\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":40035,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2023\/05\/12\/thankful-qalb\/","url_meta":{"origin":34642,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Gratitude: What kind of wealth should we acquire?","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 12, 2023","format":false,"excerpt":"Umar ibn al-Khattab reported: The Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cDestruction is in the desire for gold and silver.\u201d Umar said, \u201cO Messenger of Allah, what kind of wealth should we seek?\u201d The Prophet said, \u201cA tongue of remembrance, a grateful heart, and a believing\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":28987,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/05\/09\/umar-humility-raises-wisdom\/","url_meta":{"origin":34642,"position":4},"title":"Umar on Humility: Allah raises his wisdom if he humbles himself","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"May 9, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"\u2018Ubaydulla